title: Ask HN: Best method to classify short audio events in real time?
text:
I don't have too much experience with statistics (or ML), but a lot of the articles I've found are quite complicated for something I expected to be simple.

There are four distinct sounds I need to detect in real time with an embedded device. Think a clap sensor, but with 4 different sounding claps.

How might I go about this? How much training data (if any) do I need to collect? Is there an off-the-shelf method to just classify a few different audio events to a high degree of accuracy, and then embed that to a microcontroller (even a computer at this point)?

Thanks!

title: Ask HN: What are some communities for UI/UX design and code?
text:
I've found a few communities with great art and mockups, but they seldom have people discussing the code parts of design and those conversations are what I'm looking for.

I'd imagine that there's a lot more overlap between developers and artists, I just need to find where that's happening. Does something exist that's like a cross between HN and Dribbble?

Advice wanted on imported manufacturing equipment infected with Trojans
text:
The software to connect/calibrate the machine vision system came with some extra features we didn't request.

Are these serious issues, or common false positives?

Ulead VideoStudio 9: Trojan/Generic.ASMalwS.D2B05 ( https://www.virustotal.com/gui/file/ddf08a94800d93a5c01715d0a08c44e71c58c12821fc47d2ccb936f3391ca3fd )

Syntek STK1160 Camera/DVR Driver: Trojan.Malware.300983.susgen ( https://www.virustotal.com/gui/file/853e44510320b6e5493fdd622e0c223e64638b2ff9cdcd554333000abb47a71d )

I was mostly surprised to get decades old camera chips hidden inside.

Let me know what you think, as I've already told Santa....

Cheers, =)
